    "content": "<p>I want to be upfront: I don't have an affiliate deal with Renewed Vision. There's no commission if you click through and buy ProPresenter. I'm recommending it because it's the best tool for the job — and after 15 years of building church production systems, I've learned that recommending the second-best tool to save someone money costs them more in the long run.</p>\n\n<p>Here's the honest case for ProPresenter.</p>\n\n<h2>What Church Production Actually Requires</h2>\n\n<p>Church production has a specific set of requirements that general presentation software — PowerPoint, Keynote, even most event software — doesn't handle well.</p>\n\n<p>You're running multiple simultaneous outputs. The main screens. The stage display that shows the operator the next slide, the current clock, the pastor's notes. The lobby feed. The overflow room. The online stream gets a different look than what's on the in-room screens. All of that happening simultaneously, in real time, during a live service with no rewind button.</p>\n\n<p>You're running lyrics with automatic copyright display. You're pulling from a Bible translation library mid-service. You're rolling video without leaving the presentation interface. You're managing a live camera feed alongside your slides. And you're doing all of this with a volunteer operator who may or may not have been trained on it last week.</p>\n\n<p>That's not a PowerPoint use case. That's a ProPresenter use case.</p>\n\n<h2>What ProPresenter Does That Nothing Else Does as Well</h2>\n\n<p><strong>The stage display is the killer feature nobody talks about.</strong> Your operators see something completely different from what the congregation sees. Current slide, next slide, a running clock, pastor's notes, service order. The production team is never guessing what's coming next. This alone eliminates a category of live errors that every church production team deals with on generic software.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Eight independent content layers.</strong> ProPresenter isn't just slides — it's a layered compositor. Your background video plays on one layer. Your lyrics sit on another. An announcement graphic can be triggered as an overlay without interrupting the background. A lower third can be fired independently. Each layer is independently controllable in real time. For a production team that's used to working in layers in video software, this makes sense immediately. For a volunteer coming from PowerPoint, it's a learning curve that pays off fast.</p>\n\n<p><strong>SDI and NDI output.</strong> ProPresenter can output over SDI directly into your ATEM switcher. Or over NDI on the network. This means your graphics system is a source in your production chain just like a camera — fully integrated, cleanly switched. If your production system is built on Blackmagic and your graphics are in ProPresenter, these two talk to each other properly.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Lyrics and Bible integration that's actually built for worship.</strong> 125 Bible translations built in. CCLI SongSelect integration. Automatic copyright display. For a church doing worship every week, the time savings on lyric management and copyright compliance alone are significant. This isn't an add-on feature bolted on — it was built first, because ProPresenter was built for churches from the start.</p>\n\n<p><strong>ProContent.</strong> Renewed Vision's media library integrates directly — 50,000+ motion backgrounds, worship visuals, countdown timers, and graphic elements available inside ProPresenter without downloading and managing files manually. For churches that need consistent, high-quality visual backgrounds, this removes a logistics problem.</p>\n\n<h2>What the Alternatives Get Wrong</h2>\n\n<p>EasyWorship is the most common alternative. It's genuinely good software for smaller churches with simpler needs. Where it falls short is in output complexity and integration depth — the multi-output, multi-layer workflow that professional productions require is more limited. If you're running one screen and basic lyrics, EasyWorship works. If you're running a full production with multiple outputs, ProPresenter wins.</p>\n\n<p>Planning Center Projector is fine for what it is — a simple, affordable option that integrates tightly with Planning Center Services. But it's a minimal tool. There's no serious motion graphics layer, no SDI output, no production-grade features. For a church that's growing its production quality, you'll outgrow it.</p>\n\n<p>MediaShout exists. I've used it. It works. It doesn't have the production depth or community support that ProPresenter has built over 24 years of being the industry standard.</p>\n\n<h2>The Cost Argument</h2>\n\n<p>ProPresenter runs $29 per seat per month (or $289/year). For a church with a production computer, that's one seat. $289 per year for the production software that runs your Sunday service — the thing your congregation sees every week — is not a meaningful budget line.</p>\n\n<p>If you're running a larger operation with multiple license seats or campus needs, the Campus plan at $649/year covers 20 seats. For a multi-site church that's running ProPresenter across multiple locations, this is genuinely cost-effective.</p>\n\n<p>The free trial is 14 days and includes full functionality. There's no reason to evaluate this on spec sheets — download it, run it on your production machine, and see if it fits your workflow. It almost certainly will.</p>\n\n<h2>The Bottom Line</h2>\n\n<p>ProPresenter is what professional church production runs on. Not because Renewed Vision has the best marketing budget, but because they've been solving the specific problems of church production for 24 years and the product shows it. The stage display, the layered compositor, the SDI/NDI output, the worship integrations — these aren't coincidences. They're the result of building software specifically for this environment.</p>\n\n<p>If you're running a church production system and you're not on ProPresenter, the question is usually budget or inertia. The budget question is answered by the pricing above. The inertia question is answered by any Sunday where your current software causes a problem during a live service.</p>\n\n<p>Start the free trial. That's the whole recommendation.</p>\n\n<div style=\"background:#FEF2F2;border:2px solid #FECACA;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0;text-align:center;\">\n  <p style=\"font-weight:700;color:#B91C1C;font-size:1.05rem;margin:0 0 0.5rem;\">ProPresenter — 14-Day Free Trial</p>\n  <p style=\"color:#374151;margin:0 0 1rem;font-size:0.95rem;\">Full functionality, no credit card required. If you're building a church production system and haven't run ProPresenter yet, start here.</p>\n  <a href=\"https://renewedvision.com/propresenter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:0.7rem 1.5rem;background:#B91C1C;color:white;text-decoration:none;border-radius:0.5rem;font-weight:600;\">Start Free Trial at Renewed Vision →</a>\n</div>\n\n<p style=\"font-size:0.9rem;color:#666;text-align:center;\"><em>No affiliate relationship with Renewed Vision. Recommended because it's the right tool.</em></p>"
